Security personnel from the police and Civil Defence cordoned roads leading to the Court of Appeal in Abuja to prevent persons from staging protests against the continued involvement of the PCA, Justice Bulkachuwa in the presidential election petitions. The roads from the Nigeria Police Force (NPF) Headquarters, Federal Secretariat and Ministry of Finance were blocked by the officers in the morning causing hardship to road users. A Chief Superintendent of Police, who pleaded anonymity, told Daily Trust that the decision was to maintain sanity at the tribunal’s sitting. “It is a national duty to maintain sanity because any of the political parties might decide to take matters out of hand and anything can happen,” he said. Despite the barricades, placard-carrying PDP supporters were sighted at the road adjacent the tribunal’s premises protesting against the involvement of Justice Bulkachuwa at the tribunal. Tribunal: PDP, Atiku ask Justice Bulkachuwa to recuse self, as security personnel prevent protesters PDP protesters pass vote-of-no confidence on panel handling Atiku's petition Jos North/Bassa re-run poll: Kwande clinches seat Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin